Recursion is the process of repeating items in a self-similar way. In programming languages if a program allows you to call a function inside the same function then it is called a recursive call of the functiom.


Program
#include <stdio.h>
int power(int c, int n)
{
if(n==0)
{
return 1;
}
else
{
return x*power(x,n-1);
}
}
int main()
{
int x,n,p;
printf("Enter x and n=");
scanf("%d%d",&x,&n);
p=power(x,n);
printf("\nResult=%d",p);
return 0;
}
